## Application Entry Security (src/main.ts & src/app.module.ts)

### Application Bootstrap Security
- Configure CORS properly
- Set up security headers with helmet
- Implement global validation pipes
- Configure rate limiting
- Set up global exception filters

```typescript
// Good: Secure main.ts
async function bootstrap(): Promise<void> {
  const app = await NestFactory.create(AppModule);

  // Security headers
  app.use(helmet());

  // CORS configuration
  app.enableCors({
    origin: process.env.ALLOWED_ORIGINS?.split(',') || [],
    credentials: true
  });

  // Global validation
  app.useGlobalPipes(new ValidationPipe({
    transform: true,
    whitelist: true,
    forbidNonWhitelisted: true
  }));

  // Global exception filter
  app.useGlobalFilters(new HttpExceptionFilter());

  await app.listen(process.env.PORT || 3000);
}
```

## Testing Security (test directory)

### Security Testing
- Test authentication and authorization flows
- Test input validation and sanitization
- Test rate limiting and DoS protection
- Test error handling without information leakage
- Test with malicious inputs (SQL injection, XSS)

### Test Data Security (test/stubs)
- Use fake/mock data for tests, never real user data
- Implement test database isolation
- Clean up test data properly
- Use test-specific configurations
- Mock external services in tests

## Environment & Deployment Security

### Environment Variables
- Use different .env files for different environments
- Validate environment variables at startup
- Use strong typing for environment configurations
- Never commit .env files to version control
- Use secrets management for production

### Docker Security
- Use non-root user in Docker containers
- Update .dockerignore to exclude sensitive files
- Use multi-stage builds to minimize image size
- Scan Docker images for vulnerabilities
- Use specific base image versions, not 'latest'

### Serverless Security
- Implement proper IAM roles and policies
- Use environment-specific serverless configurations
- Monitor function execution and costs
- Implement cold start security considerations
- Use VPC for database connections

## Monitoring & Compliance

### Security Monitoring
- Log all authentication attempts
- Monitor failed authorization attempts
- Track unusual access patterns
- Monitor configuration changes
- Implement real-time alerting for security events

### Compliance Requirements
- Implement GDPR data handling (right to deletion, data portability)
- Add audit trails for all data modifications
- Implement data retention policies
- Provide user consent management
- Regular security assessments and penetration testing

## Emergency Response

### Security Incident Response
- Implement graceful degradation for security incidents
- Have rollback procedures for compromised deployments
- Implement emergency access controls
- Document incident response procedures
- Regular security drills and training

### Data Breach Response
- Implement immediate containment procedures
- Have user notification templates ready
- Document all security events for compliance
- Implement forensic logging for investigation
- Regular backup and recovery testing
